message.text:
Summer Holidays!
 It is the longest vacation in a year for school boys & girls in Japan, full of fun and excitements...if there were no summer HOMEWORKS!
 The typical summer homeworks for Japanese children are, for example, picture diaries（えにっき、絵日記）, book reports（どくしょかんそうぶん、読書感想文）, astronomical observations（てんたいかんそく、天体観測）, summer holiday research projects（じゆうけんきゅう、自由研究） and so on.
 Japanese learners, how about joining in our summer events and writing diaries about them in Japanese? This "homework" will surely brush up your Japanese skills!
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1557,488&p=1&q=%E5%AE%BF%E9%A1%8C&source=search&lang=en

message.text:
Today is "Day of Chopsticks"（箸の日、はしのひ）! 
“August 4th” is read as ha (８) shi (４) in Japanese that together sound the same as hashi(箸、はし) meaning "chopsticks".

It is said that approx. 30% of people in the world use chopsticks mainly in Asia. Different countries have different styles & rules, and there are many strict DON'TS in Japan too.

How many chopstick-rules do you know? 
DON'TS Example:"Mayoi-bashi(迷い箸、まよいばし）" 
"Do not hover chopsticks over the dishes while humming and hawing about what to eat."
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1871,762&p=1&q=%E3%81%AF%E3%81%97&source=search&lang=en

８月４日は箸の日！世界では30％がお箸を使っているといわれていて、国によって様々なスタイルやルールがあります。日本のやってはいけないお箸のルール、あなたはいくつ知っていますか？
「迷い箸」はいけませんよ～。
